# Day 4 - HTTP vs HTTPS Analysis

## Objective
Understand the difference between HTTP and HTTPS using Wireshark.

## What I Learned

- HTTP stands for HyperText Transfer Protocol.
- HTTPS stands for HyperText Transfer Protocol Secure.
- HTTP traffic is readable.
- HTTPS traffic is encrypted using TLS.
- GET requests are used by the browser to request web resources.
- 200 OK indicates that the server successfully processed the request.
- Security Analysts can inspect metadata in encrypted traffic even though the content remains protected.

## Practical

- Captured HTTP traffic using http://neverssl.com
- Captured HTTPS traffic using ChatGPT.
- Compared HTTP GET requests with encrypted TLS Application Data.

